tool_description: OpenIndoor API returns OSM indoor data in MVT format
name: Indoor data
title: Indoor data

api_list.name: getFromMapLayer
api_list.description:
Will return a vector tile with a single layer from the provided {map} at the provided {z}, {x} and {y} values.

    - {map} is one of our defined maps.
    - {layer} is the name of one of the defined maps layers.
    - {z} is the tile zoom.
    - {x} is the tile row.
    - {y} is the tile column.
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://indoor-data.p.rapidapi.com/maps/openindoor/tours/13/8091/8091"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "indoor-data.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())
api_list.convert_code:
import requests

url = "https://indoor-data.p.rapidapi.com/maps/{maps}/{layer}/{z}/{x}/{y}"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "indoor-data.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())
